This paper deals with the interpretation of deep neural network decisions, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed method, Rectified Gradient, involves layer-wise thresholding during backpropagation, which is a technique commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the effectiveness of the method in experiments with image datasets, which is a common application in natural language processing (cs.CL) and computer vision (cs.CV).
